<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-3345] SMTP: &quot;from&quot; in URI ignored?</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-3345</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In my quick test with GMail, the &quot;from&quot; in a Mail URI was ignored:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;to uri=&quot;smtps:smtp.gmail.com?username=ammulder@gmail.com&amp;amp; amp;password=guess&amp;amp;from=Aaron Mulder &amp;amp; lt;ammulder@apache.org&amp;amp; gt;&amp;amp; amp;debugMode=true&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I couldn&apos;t find any code that reads the &quot;from&quot; out of the URI and sets it on the &lt;tt&gt;MailConfiguration&lt;/tt&gt;, though I see that &lt;tt&gt;MailBinding&lt;/tt&gt; will use a &quot;from&quot; on the MailConfiguration if it&apos;s there.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not 100% sure that GMail isn&apos;t just denying the request to send from a registered alternate address, but not being able to find the code makes me suspicious.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
